From: Thomas Zimmermann <tzimmermann@suse.de>
Date: Tue, 24 Sep 2024 09:12:50 +0200
Subject: drm/cirrus: Run DRM default client setup
Git-commit: c8d7b065f2f802a73fd444dd30f90e43c172a5a6
Patch-mainline: v6.13-rc1
References: jsc#PED-13979 jsc#PED-14039 jsc#PED-14046 jsc#PED-14211 jsc#PED-14333 jsc#PED-14487 jsc#PED-14488 jsc#PED-14497 jsc#PED-14499

Call drm_client_setup() to run the kernel's default client setup
for DRM. Set fbdev_probe in struct drm_driver, so that the client
setup can start the common fbdev client.

The cirrus driver requests the same client pixel format as the value
stored in struct drm_mode_config.preferred_depth. The fbdev client
also looks at this value for the default pixel format. Thus remove
the format selection from cirrus.

V5: 
- select DRM_CLIENT_SELECTION

Signed-off-by: Thomas Zimmermann <tzimmermann@suse.de>
Cc: Dave Airlie <airlied@redhat.com>
Cc: Gerd Hoffmann <kraxel@redhat.com>
Acked-by: Javier Martinez Canillas <javierm@redhat.com>
Link: https://patchwork.freedesktop.org/patch/msgid/20240924071734.98201-53-tzimmermann@suse.de
Acked-by: Patrik Jakobsson <pjakobsson@suse.de>

---
 drivers/gpu/drm/tiny/Kconfig  | 1 +
 drivers/gpu/drm/tiny/cirrus.c | 4 +++-
 2 files changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/tiny/Kconfig b/drivers/gpu/drm/tiny/Kconfig
index 5e047ba8a30d..d6194296d6da 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/tiny/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/tiny/Kconfig
@@ -26,6 +26,7 @@ config DRM_BOCHS
 config DRM_CIRRUS_QEMU
 	tristate "Cirrus driver for QEMU emulated device"
 	depends on DRM && PCI && MMU
+	select DRM_CLIENT_SELECTION
 	select DRM_KMS_HELPER
 	select DRM_GEM_SHMEM_HELPER
 	help
diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/tiny/cirrus.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/tiny/cirrus.c
index e31e1df029ab..18df8f8b65ad 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/tiny/cirrus.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/tiny/cirrus.c
@@ -27,6 +27,7 @@
 #include <drm/drm_atomic.h>
 #include <drm/drm_atomic_helper.h>
 #include <drm/drm_atomic_state_helper.h>
+#include <drm/drm_client_setup.h>
 #include <drm/drm_connector.h>
 #include <drm/drm_damage_helper.h>
 #include <drm/drm_drv.h>
@@ -664,6 +665,7 @@ static const struct drm_driver cirrus_driver = {
 
 	.fops		 = &cirrus_fops,
 	DRM_GEM_SHMEM_DRIVER_OPS,
+	DRM_FBDEV_SHMEM_DRIVER_OPS,
 };
 
 static int cirrus_pci_probe(struct pci_dev *pdev,
@@ -718,7 +720,7 @@ static int cirrus_pci_probe(struct pci_dev *pdev,
 	if (ret)
 		return ret;
 
-	drm_fbdev_shmem_setup(dev, 16);
+	drm_client_setup(dev, NULL);
 	return 0;
 }
 
